<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Item&nbsp;8.01.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Other Events. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%;padding-bottom:3px;line-height:95%; vertical-align:top"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On April&nbsp;6, 2009, Bristol-Myers Squibb Company (the &#147;Company&#148;) issued a press release announcing an agreement with Otsuka Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd. (&#147;Otsuka&#148;) to extend the U.S. portion of the
companies&#146; long-standing agreement for the development and commercialization of ABILIFY<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP>&reg;</SUP></FONT> (aripiprazole) from the currently scheduled end date of November 2012 until the expected loss
of exclusivity in April 2015. In addition, the Company announced that it and Otsuka have established an oncology collaboration for two Bristol-Myers Squibb products, SPRYCEL<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP>&reg;</SUP></FONT> (dasatinib)
and IXEMPRA<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP>&reg;</SUP></FONT> (ixabepilone). The Company also announced that it is confirming its previously disclosed full year 2009 earnings per share (&#147;EPS&#148;) guidance on a GAAP basis, 2009 EPS
guidance on a non-GAAP basis, and non-GAAP EPS compounded annual growth rate guidance from 2007 through 2010, subject to certain assumptions, and that it expects a minimum $0.30 EPS accretion in 2013 and 2014 from this agreement. A copy of the press
release is furnished as Exhibit 99.1 to this report and incorporated herein by reference. Also furnished and incorporated by reference as Exhibit 99.2 is certain supplemental information posted on the Company&#146;s website at <U>www.bms.com</U>.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<FILENAME>dex991.htm
<DESCRIPTION>PRESS RELEASE
<TEXT>
<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Press release</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>BRISTOL-MYERS SQUIBB ANNOUNCES EXTENSION OF </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>U.S. AGREEMENT FOR ABILIFY AND </B></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ESTABLISHMENT OF AN ONCOLOGY COLLABORATION WITH OTSUKA </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><I>Agreement extends a highly successful neuroscience collaboration to 2015 and expands strategic collaboration into oncology </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2"><B><I>Company confirms 2009 GAAP EPS guidance of $1.58 - $1.73 and non-GAAP EPS guidance of $1.85 - $2.00 </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><I>Company confirms
2007-2010 15% non-GAAP EPS CAGR and expects minimum $0.30 accretion in 2013 and 2014 </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:3px;line-height:95%; vertical-align:top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">Princeton, New Jersey, April 6, 2009 &#150; Bristol-Myers Squibb Company (NYSE: BMY) today announced an agreement with Otsuka Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd. (hereafter, &#147;Otsuka&#148;) to extend the U.S. portion of the companies&#146;
long-standing agreement for the development and commercialization of ABILIFY<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP>&reg;</SUP></FONT> (aripiprazole) from the currently scheduled end date of November 2012 until the expected loss of exclusivity in
April 2015. In addition, the companies have established an oncology collaboration for two Bristol-Myers Squibb products &#150; SPRYCEL<FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP>&reg;</SUP></FONT> (dasatinib) and IXEMPRA<FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="1"><SUP>&reg;</SUP></FONT> (ixabepilone). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;The announcement today is further evidence that Bristol-Myers Squibb is delivering on its
commitments to advance its transformation to a leading next-generation BioPharma,&#148; said Lamberto Andreotti, president and chief operating officer, Bristol-Myers Squibb. &#147;The agreement with out long standing and valued collaborator Otsuka
will help build our earnings base for 2013 and transition us to an expected period of growth in 2014 and beyond. Further, our balance sheet remains strong, which allows us to pursue business development opportunities as part of our String of Pearls
strategy.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;We are very pleased to continue our important work with Otsuka on ABILIFY. Our collaboration to develop this medicine that helps
people with serious mental disorders has resulted in it becoming one of the industry&#146;s most successful products,&#148; he continued. &#147;The expanded agreement also provides an opportunity for Bristol-Myers Squibb and Otsuka to work together
in oncology. We believe that sharing our collective resources will benefit the cancer patients we serve.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B><U>Agreement Terms </U></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Under terms of the agreement Bristol-Myers Squibb will pay Otsuka an up-front cash payment of $400 million. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Beginning on January&nbsp;1, 2010, the share of ABILIFY U.S. net sales Bristol-Myers Squibb will receive will change from 65% to: </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">58% for 2010; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">During this period Otsuka will be responsible for 30% of expenses related to the commercialization of ABILIFY compared to having no responsibility under the
existing collaboration agreement. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Beginning January&nbsp;1, 2013, and through the expected loss of US exclusivity in 2015, Bristol-Myers Squibb will receive 50% of net sales up to $2.7 billion and a
declining tiered share of net sales above $2.7 billion. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Beginning in 2010, Bristol-Myers Squibb and Otsuka will collaborate on two oncology assets SPRYCEL and IXEMPRA as follows: </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P
STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Otsuka will share in commercial expenses for the U.S., Europe and Japan and co-promote SPRYCEL with Bristol-Myers Squibb in the U.S., Japan and major EU markets;
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Bristol-Myers Squibb will pay Otsuka a collaboration fee on aggregate annual net sales of SPRYCEL and IXEMPRA beginning in 2010 on a regressive tiering basis
through 2020. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To provide details on the extended agreement and related financial updates, Bristol-Myers Squibb will hold an investor
call today at 8:30 a.m. For details, please visit the Bristol-Myers Squibb web site www.bms.com/ir. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Bristol-Myers Squibb is a global biopharmaceutical
company whose mission is to extend and enhance human life. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Financial Guidance and Long-Term Outlook </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>The financial guidance and long-term outlook provided in this press release are based upon current expectations and exclude specified items, the impact of any
potential strategic transactions and the current global economic downturn/crisis. The long-term outlook further assumes that the Company and Otsuka maintain U.S. exclusivity for the Abilify patent through at least 2014. </I></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Use of Non-GAAP Financial Information </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>This press release contains non-GAAP financial measures, including non-GAAP earnings per share, adjusted to exclude certain costs, expenses, gains and losses and other specified items. This information is intended
to enhance an investor&#146;s overall understanding of the company&#146;s past financial performance and prospects for the future. For example, non-GAAP earnings per share information is an indication of the company&#146;s baseline performance
before items that are considered by the company to be not reflective of the company&#146;s ongoing results. In addition, this information is among the primary indicators the company uses as a basis for evaluating company performance, allocating
resources, setting incentive compensation targets, and planning and forecasting future periods. This information is not intended to be considered in isolation or as a substitute for diluted earnings per share prepared in accordance with GAAP. </I>
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Reconciliations of GAAP to non-GAAP financial measures are available on the company&#146;s website at bms.com. </I></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Forward-Looking Statement </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>This press release contains
&#147;forward-looking statements&#148; as that term is defined in the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995, regarding the research, development and commercialization of pharmaceutical products.&nbsp;Such forward-looking statements are
based on current expectations and involve inherent risks and uncertainties, including factors that could delay, divert or change any of them, and could cause actual outcomes and results to differ materially from current expectations.&nbsp;No
forward-looking statement can be guaranteed.&nbsp;Forward-looking statements in the press release should be evaluated together with the many uncertainties that affect Bristol-Myers Squibb&#146;s business, particularly those identified in the
cautionary factors discussion in Bristol-Myers Squibb&#146;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2008, its Quarterly Reports on Form 10-Q, and Current Reports on Form 8-K.&nbsp;Bristol-Myers Squibb undertakes no
obligation to publicly update any forward-looking statement, whether as a result of new information, future events, or otherwise. </I></FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
